These four standards are further expanded upon in The Code and include gaining consent, adhering to professional boundaries, working effectively as part of a team and delegation appropriately to others, keeping knowledge and skills up to date, maintaining clear and accurate records and upholding the reputation of the profession at all times. The Code reaffirms the registrant's personal accountability for their actions and omissions and being able to justify their decisions. Furthermore, the registrant's actions should always be lawful whether these relate to their professional or personal life. A registrant who does not practise according to these standards could find themselves before the NMC's Practice Committees with a possible suspension from practice and/or removal from the professional Register.
