\section*{CONCLUSION}

Embryonic and fetal development occurs alongside placental development. There is constant growth and remodelling of cells, tissues, organs and systems prior to birth. Several temporary structures in the fetus support systems in utero; these consequently become redundant at birth and they either disappear or become ligaments. At birth all organs are functioning but some may be immature and continue to develop as part of extrauterine life.

