\section*{First stage of labour}

Upon diagnosis of a face presentation, the midwife should inform the doctor of this deviation from the normal. Routine observations of maternal and fetal conditions are made as in a normal physiological labour (see Chapter 16). A fetal scalp electrode must not be applied, and care

