\section*{Immediate action}

Where the diagnosis of cord prolapse is made, the time should be noted and the midwife must call for urgent assistance. The midwife should explain to the woman and her birth partner her findings and any emergency measures that may be needed. If an oxytocin infusion is in progress this should be discontinued. If the cord lies outside the vagina, then it should be gently replaced to prevent spasm, to maintain temperature and prevent drying. Administering oxygen to the woman by face mask at $4 \mathrm{l} / \mathrm{min}$ may improve fetal oxygenation.

\section*{Relieving pressure on the cord}

