Positive benefits for mothers and their families who live within the designated postcode for Children's Centre services have been reported (Tanner et al 2012). However, a sustained commitment to service provision and funding is essential for this to benefit mothers and their families. In 2009, Children's Centres became a statutory requirement under the Apprenticeships, Skills, Children and

