- Do not offer to remove the baby. Separating mother and baby, particularly removing the baby at night in the mistaken belief that the mother will benefit if she does not wake to breastfeed her baby at night, is strongly correlated with reduced breastfeeding success (WHO, 1998).
- If the mother asks you to, and you agree to take the baby away to settle, return the baby to her when he wakes again to be fed.
