Supplementary feeds are feeds given in place of a breastfeed. There is no justification for their use except in exceptional circumstances, such as severe illness or unconsciousness. This is because each breastfeed that is missed by the baby interferes with the establishment of lactation and affects the mother's confidence in being able to successfully breastfeed her baby.

